      "titleText": "🖥️ Lab Environment Setup",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "New here? Don't worry — this section walks you through everything step by step. No experience needed.",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "When learning security, you don't want to practice on your real computer. Instead, you set up a virtual machine (VM) — think of it as a computer inside your computer. You can break it, reset it, or delete it without touching your actual system.",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "tableData": {
        "headers": [],
        "rows": []
      },
      "codeText": "",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": true,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showTable": false,
      "showCode": false,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "slide-r"
    },
    {
      "id": "3a4af319-eb30-4efd-9a57-74686cd4702f",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#030803 0%,#061206 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Step 1 — Pick an Operating System",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "Security tools mostly run on Linux. You don't need to install Linux on your real machine — you'll run it inside a VM (explained in Step 2).\nIf you're a complete beginner → start with Kali Linux. It comes with everything preinstalled.",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "tableData": {
        "headers": [
          "OS",
          "Best for",
          "Download"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "Kali Linux",
            "Beginners — 600+ security tools preinstalled, tons of guides online",
            "ISO / VM image"
          ],
          [
            "Parrot OS",
            "Beginners who want something lighter than Kali",
            "ISO / VM image"
          ],
          [
            "BlackArch",
            "Experienced users — 3000+ tools, Arch-based",
            "ISO / VM image"
          ],
          [
            "Garuda Linux",
            "Arch users who want a nice desktop and can add BlackArch tools",
            "ISO"
          ],
          [
            "Arch Linux",
            "Advanced users who want to build everything from scratch",
            "ISO / VM image"
          ]
        ]
      },
      "codeText": "",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
